commit.message: workflow: Disable ds24909 -- depends on old libusb
workflow: Try running result with a glob
workflow: Fix matrix substitution
workflow: Fix typo
workflow: Add a build and test workflow

test_build_af: Add PASS/FAIL to test output

Also collect the results and return 0 for success and 1 for fail to the
caller. Exit with this code instead of continuing to execute.
build_af: Tweak code to match style of the other build_ functions

digitemp: Style cleanup

Also adds missing -V log option to help
Fix typo in usage().

Improved support for DS2438 measurements: output of Vsense via the %J token
in ADC output format (code, test code, prototypes and man page).

Added support for output format for DS2438:
* added option -V to provide output format, using token %Q for the value of
  Vdd measurement and token %q for the input voltage Vad
* added format building function build_af() observing output buffer length
  to avoid possible buffer overruns
* updated usage() output and man page accordingly
README: Add note about Linux ds2490 kernel driver problems

check_digitemp.pl: Add support for multiple sensors

Thanks to Martin Tettke for adding support for a file to map sensors to
names, and reading all sensors instead of just one.
New version - 3.7.2
Fix digitemp.spec Version in bumpver target
Make sure strncpy uses are null-terminated

Add a check for ROM number vs. SENSORS count

Closes #25

Log the scratchpad diagnostics

This was never hooked up to print/log. Closes GH issue #18
Bump Copyright Year to 2018

Fix strftime use of log_file

It wasn't working if the log_file format string was read from the
rcfile.

Add strftime formating to logfile name

eg. -ltemperature-%Y%m%d.txt
Clean up the start_time switch statement usage

Add log_type 4 & 5

Use unixtime instead of elapsed time

Check for bad Get_Temperature result

and refactor read_ds2438 a bunch. Adopt the same loop as the humidity
read, and instead of skipping output on A/D reading failure output the
failed readings. When using -o2 or -o3 this will still output the
temperature if the A/D readings fail.

Fix the return value of Get_Temperature in ad26.c

Returning FALSE for a double doesn't do a good job of indicating an
error. Use -999.0 instead.

Display DS2438 temperature even if humidity calculation fails.

Previously, if the DS2438 is not a humidity sensor, it would skip
displaying it unless -A is passed. But it still has a useful temperature
so this changes it to always output the results, but the humidity will
be 0%

Always include types.h and time.h

digitemp.c was already unconditionally including these, so just add them
to ownet.h

Bump copyright year to 2016

Happy 20th digitemp!

Add bumpver target

The version source is the digitemp.spec Version: string, and bumpver
will increment the .Z update the changelog of the spec as well as other
references to the version in README, COPYRIGHT, and digitemp.h

Spelling corrections

Correct occured -> occurred as found by lintian.

A previous commit fixed some other spelling errors, but that was just in
binary output (which lintian could easily detect).  This also goes back
and corrects comments/docs/etc with those found errors.
